VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT badCertificateCallback\s*=|onBadCertificate\s*=
WHEN EXPR MISSING:test|development|localhost|staging|// intentional|badCertificateCallback.*throw
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects custom HTTP client callbacks that may bypass certificate validation.
TRACE Externalized mobile rule logic for Ignoring TLS Certificate Errors.
